 MBOMBELA – CCTV footage of suspects breaking into a bakkie at Westend Shopping Centre has emerged. The bakkie was driven by Dawid Theron and belonged to Daisy Business Solutions. Theron said he parked the bakkie at around 19:30 on Monday and went inside the centre to grab some take-aways. He said on his return, he noticed that something was missing from the bakkie.  Also Read:VIDEO: CIT robbers hit Fidelity vehicle in Mbombela “The suspects broke the lock on the passenger’s door and stole a technician tool box to the value of about R6 000 to R8 000 and some copier toner cartridges. The items were kept behind the driver’s seat,” said Theron. The suspects could be seen on CCTV getting away in a silver VW Polo sedan. Callum MacPherson, of Hi-Tech Security, said they have identified the suspects and were expecting to make arrests soon. Also Read: CIT robbers shoot man on school run “We advise motorists not to leave their valuable items in their cars. We further urge the public to report this vehicle wherever they see it, as it has been involved in many crime incidents around shopping centres in Mbombela,” said MacPherson.